        h2#HowToUse How To Use
        p.
          This site is a fun way to interact with the movie ratings and director information from the IMDB.
          If you're trying to find out the best director, or if one director is better than another, can you use
          this data to answer that question? Perhaps.
        p.
          It's easy to ask analytical questions about the data, a little harder to justify calling the results
          a list of "the best" or "better than. As long as we don't take the results too seriously, we can use
          this analysis to find out some interesting relationships about some of our favorite directors and their
          films and to discover some names and movies that we've never heard of before.
        h2#Examples Examples
        p.
          Let's start with <a href="http://bestdirectors.netrc.com/?minNumVotes=10&minNumFilms=10"> min num votes set to 10 and min num films set to 10 </a>. There
          are a lot of people.
          One cogent suggest for best director would be more than 10 movies with a substantial following, lets say more than 500 votes. After all, a great director
          may only make a modest number of films.
          Or you might say that a great director will have made a lot of good-to-great movies. How many is a lot? Tring 30 movies with 500.
          Let's look for some people that make lots and lots of movies, 100 votes and 50 movies.
